The evidence with the title 'Mothers who receive food stamps ' says Oct 31, 2011  ... In summer 1993 , there were 36 million mothers of childbearing ages (15 to 44 years old ) living in the United States; 5.3 million of them (15 percent) were receiving food  ... Two in every three mothers on food stamps had their first birth out - of- wedlock, compared with about 1 in 4 who were not on food stamps. 
